  "texts": [
    "Thus, the coded information in the amino-acid sequence does not provide the full spectrum of information of the protein.",
    "The environment is also relevant in determining its information content.",
    "One protein might be a structural protein in a membrane, and the other might be an enzyme, thus encoding very different information that is responsible for very different functions and behavior.",
    "How do we measure the difference between these informations?",
    "The qualitative differences in the amino-acid sequence can account for part of this difference and can be quanti ed; but it provides only a partial description of the information relevant to the system.Fuzzy Information is a concept that is relevant when assessing interactions between systems and between systems and their environments."
